.TH "devm_platform_get_and_ioremap_resource" 9 "devm_platform_get_and_ioremap_resource" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_platform_get_and_ioremap_resource \- call devm_ioremap_resource() for a platform device and get resource
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void __iomem *" devm_platform_get_and_ioremap_resource
.BI "(struct platform_device *pdev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int index "  ","
.BI "struct resource **res "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
platform device to use both for memory resource lookup as well as
resource management
.IP "index" 12
resource index
.IP "res" 12
optional output parameter to store a pointer to the obtained resource.
.SH "RETURN"
a pointer to the remapped memory or an \fBERR_PTR\fP encoded error code
on failure.
